text_blocks.snippet: Kanye West is 48 years old, having been born on June 8, 1977.
He is widely regarded as one of the most influential figures in modern music, transitioning from a background producer to a global solo artist.

list.snippet: Record Producer (Master Proficiency): His core skill. He is famous for his "chipmunk soul" sampling technique—pitching up vocal samples—and is often ranked as one of the greatest producers of all time.

Rapper/Vocalist (High Proficiency): Known for his unique flow and cadence. While some critics debate his technical "flow" compared to peers, he is praised for his vulnerability, humor, and emotional delivery.
Songwriter (Expert Proficiency): He is credited on almost all his work and has written for numerous other industry icons like Jay-Z and Alicia Keys.
Pianist (Self-Taught Proficiency): Though not classically trained, he uses the piano as a foundational tool for songwriting and live performances, often seen playing it during events.
Composer/Arranger (Master Proficiency): Noted for his ability to blend diverse genres, from industrial minimalism to soaring orchestral arrangements.

Details: As of early 2026, West primarily resides in an ultra-private, $35 million mansion in the exclusive Beverly North Park gated community. While he maintains properties elsewhere, including a childhood home in Chicago and interests in Japan, this Beverly Hills estate is his primary domestic base.
